            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The fragment is unpublished. The use of rhomboid omicron strongly suggests the text was originally in Greek, and given the archaeological context, namely the necropolis in the area of via Dott. Consoli, the fragment is most likely to be part of a Greek funerary inscription of the imperial period. The text potentially comes from the first line given the vacat above.</p>
            </div>
